Okay, I understand that navigating relationship challenges can feel overwhelming and like there's no way out. Many couples do experience times where frustration builds up and it starts to snowball, especially if communication becomes stalled or repeated resolution attempts don't help. You're definitely not the first person to feel this sense of permanent stagnation in a relationship that feels stuck. Before you decide to make major changes in your life, I'd actually recommend taking some quality time to step away from the dynamics before wasting time making larger life decisions. When people feel especially overwhelmed, clarity and relief can often come from taking things off your back, even if only temporarily.

In the short term, I'd recommend starting by writing down everything you're feeling right now, particularly anything that's been bothering you that hasn't been resolved by calling a practical day. When you get really angry about how badly you've been treated, it's wise to take some quality time to process your feelings completely before manipulating situations or creating new conflicts.
